<TEXT>
<P>
 WITNESS: Endangered Species of North America by Susan Middleton & David 
Liittschwager (Chronicle Books: $29.95; 256 pp., paperback original). So many 
books on endangered species have appeared in recent years, they practically 
constitute a genre, but the virtuoso beauty of "Witness" stands out among them. 
Middleton and Liittschwager photographed single animals and plants, which 
imbues the pictures with the dignity of fine portraiture: Instead of an 
undifferentiated group of wolves or salmon, they show the reader an individual, 
underscoring its unique genetic heritage. "Witness" is an eloquent record of 
beautiful creatures that may soon exist only in photographs. 
</P>
