</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 MAGAZINE WARS: Another periodical with a battle on its hands -- in fact, two 
battles -- is the hip-hop monthly the Source.Public Enemy has made its new 
video for the song "I Stand Accused" a vicious spoof of the magazine -- renamed 
"the Soft" in the video -- in retaliation for a negative review of PE's recent 
"Muse Sick N Hour Mess Age" album.  
</P>
<P>
 Like the Source, the magazine depicted in the video has a white publisher and 
editor, a circumstance that PE mocks as being out of touch with African 
American culture. A representative for PE confirmed that the video targets the 
Source, but would not comment further. Steve Hochman 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
