<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOUR-STAR FILMS; 'THE DEVIL AND DANIEL WEBSTER' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Michael Wilmington 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Stephen Vincent Benet's New England version of "Faust," with the Devil (Walter 
Huston, left, as the wickedly gleeful Mr. Scratch) battling oratorical genius 
Daniel Webster (Edward Arnold, right) for the soul of farmer James Craig. Benet 
wrote the script, and director William Dieterle and cinematographer Joe August 
had a field day, bringing back all the shadowy delights of German 
Expressionism. With a score by Bernard Herrmann (Showtime Tuesday at 3:30 
p.m.). 
</P>
<P>
 Other four-star films airing this week: 
</P>
<P>
 Going My Way AMC, Sunday, 10:05 a.m., 7:35 p.m.; Monday, 3 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Paths of Glory Showtime, Monday, 11:05 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 His Girl Friday Disney Channel, Monday, 9 p.m., Tuesday, 3:15 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Major Barbara Bravo, Wednesday, 2:30 p.m., Thursday, 12:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Rosemary's Baby Bravo, Friday, 7 p.m., Saturday, 10 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The African Queen TBS, Saturday, 5 p.m. Michael Wilmington 
