<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Steve Hochman 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 DO IT YOURSELF: Rhino Records is acknowledged as one of the best, if not the 
best, packager of compilations.So it's hard to figure why Rhino executives 
would want your help. But they do. 
</P>
<P>
 As part of its "Sweet 16" anniversary, Rhino is holding a contest in 
conjunction with Tower Records for the best concept for a compilation album. 
The winner -- to be selected on the basis of creativity, commercial viability 
and feasibility (i.e. the licensing availability of material) -- will get 
compiler-producer credit and fees for the album. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm expecting the entries to be an equal mix of serious and humorous 
approaches," says Rhino vice president Gary Stewart. "But we'll consider 
anything that's viable." Steve Hochman 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
