<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SMALL FACES: With only football to keep him busy now that baseball's on 
strike, dual-sport star Deion Sanders is doing some rapping, teaming with 
Hammer for "Straight to the Feet," a track from the soundtrack to the upcoming 
Jean-Claude Van Damme action film "Street Fighter." Van Damme will join the two 
to shoot a video soon. Among others contributing new tracks to the album, due 
from Priority Records on Dec. 6, are Ice Cube, Public Enemy, LL Cool J and the 
Pharcyde. The movie will be in theaters Dec. 23. . . . 
</P>
<P>
 Los Lobos is doing a song and the instrumental score for "El Mariachi II," a 
film by Robert Rodriguez, and is finishing up work on a children's album. 
Meanwhile, the band has started to write for a new "regular" group album, with 
recording set to begin around New Year's. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 English soul-dance group Massive Attack's second album, "Protection," is due 
Jan. 24. Nicolette is the act's new lead singer, with Shara Nelson having moved 
on to a solo career. Everything but the Girl's Tracey Thorn also guests on two 
tracks, while reggae veteran Horace Randy sings a version of the Doors' "Light 
My Fire." . . .  
</P>
<P>
 Collective Soul is working on its second album, due in March, and has a new 
song, "Gel," set for the soundtrack to the Jerky Boys' upcoming film debut, due 
in February. . . . John Hiatt will begin recording a new album in November, 
using the Guilty Dogs, the same hard-edged band that accompanied him on the 
road recently and is heard on the live album, "Hiatt Comes Alive at Budokan?" 
due next month. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 Don Was is set to produce the third album by the Highwaymen -- the country 
supergroup consisting of Willie Nelson, Waylon Jennings, Johnny Cash and Kris 
Kristofferson. They'll start recording in December. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 The long-awaited follow-up to rap group Black Sheep's 1991 hit debut album is 
finally set for mid-November. . . . The latest curve on the Internet features 
discount coupons for the recent Van Morrison tribute album, which users can 
download, print and redeem at Tower Records stores. Audio and video clips from 
the album can also be accessed. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 A documentary on Texas psychedelic-rock cult hero Roky Erikson will be 
released on home video on Halloween. "Demon Angel: A Day and Night With Roky 
Erikson" was taped by Mike Alvarez in Austin and features Erikson performing 
acoustic versions of songs, including his old 13th Floor Elevators hit "You're 
Gonna Miss Me." It also includes interviews with relatives and associates. . . 
. 
</P>
<P>
 Enya's next new album has been pushed back to early next year, but the singer 
is remastering an old album, "The Celts," which will be repackaged for release 
sometime this year, possibly with a new song added. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 Erotic poems of Erica Jong have been set to music for an upcoming album by 
techno artist Vanessa Daou, with Jong herself making a spoken-word appearance 
on one track. . . . Timbuk 3 (of "The Future's So Bright, I Gotta Wear Shades" 
fame) has a new album due in January from Windham Hill's High Street label. 
</P>
