<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 DINNER WITH LINDA: Paul McCartney has sold more than 100 million records as 
part of the Beatles, Wings and as a solo artist. Now his wife, Linda, has also 
sold that amount . . . of frozen vegetarian dinners.Yes, her line of meatless 
meals (recently introduced in the United States) is now the biggest-selling of 
its kind in Great Britain. 
</P>
<P>
 For some reason, the company that markets them decided we'd need some physical 
comparisons to understand how many dinners that really is. Figuring on three 
veggie sausages per dinner, a press release tells us, those 100 million dinners 
would, laid end to end, stretch from London to Australia and back. 
</P>
<P>
 Still can't see it? OK -- stacked on top of each other they would be as high 
as 431 Mt. Everests. Not good enough? Trucks carrying 100 million meals would 
stretch 12 miles. 
</P>
<P>
 Wonder how many McDonald's you could build from them? 
</P>
</TEXT>
