<HEADLINE>
<P>
RERUNS TO REWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Very Very Nick at Nite (Sunday at 8:30 p.m. on Nickelodeon) presents "Very 
Very Tearjerkers," featuring four emotional episodes of "The Mary Tyler Moore 
Show." 
</P>
<P>
 TNT presents six episodes of the camp '70s series CHiPS (Monday beginning at 7 
a.m.); Eric Estrada stars. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Goulet guests on Police Story (Monday at 9 a.m. on A&E) in an episode 
in which two narcotics detectives give up a fun-filled weekend to pursue a 
major drug dealer. 
</P>
<P>
 Ray Milland plays a collector of rare plants who murders his nephew for his 
money on Columbo (Sunday at 11 a.m. on A&E). 
</P>
<P>
 The great Charlie Ruggles plays Aunt Clara's old flame on Bewitched (Monday at 
8 p.m. on Nickelodeon). 
</P>
<P>
 Dean Stockwell and Jerry Lee Lewis guest on Police Story (Friday at 3 p.m. on 
A&E) in an episode about a male chauvinist cop who becomes upset when a woman 
officer is assigned to him. 
</P>
<P>
 Morgan Fairchild appears on The Bob Newhart Show (Friday at 9:30 p.m. on 
Nickelodeon) in an episode in which Bob and Emily celebrate their 10th wedding 
anniversary. 
</P>
<P>
 Eileen Heckart ("The Five Mrs. Buchanans") plays Mary's Aunt Flo, a 
globe-trotting journalist, who falls for Lou on The Mary Tyler Moore Show 
(Friday at 10 p.m. on Nickelodeon). 
</P>
<P>
 Nick at Nite repeats the hilarious, Emmy Award-winning "Chuckles Bites the 
Dust" episode of The Mary Tyler Moore Show (Friday at 10:30 p.m. on 
Nickelodeon). 
</P>
<P>
 Lucy feels like going on an excursion to find Uranium when she visits Las 
Vegas on The Lucy & Desi Comedy Hour (Saturday at 11 p.m. on Nickelodeon); Fred 
MacMurray and his wife June Haver are guests. 
</P>
