<HEADLINE>
<P>
KENNEDY GRAVE SITE AGAIN OPEN TO PUBLIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The grave site that holds the remains of President John F. Kennedy and his 
wife was reopened to public viewing Friday, refurbished to include a marker for 
Jacqueline Bouvier Kennedy Onassis, who died last May. 
</P>
<P>
 The grave site in Arlington National Cemetery had been closed for two days 
while the new marker was added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
