East Rutherford, N.J. The victory snapped a three-game losing streak for the 
Scarlet Knights (3-3) and dropped Army to 1-4, its worst start since opening 
the 1974 season 1-5. . . . Columbia stretched its unbeaten streak to three 
games, longest in more than 20 years, and handed winless Fordham its sixth 
consecutive defeat with a 24-13 victory at New York. The victory gave the Lions 
a 2-1-1 record, their best since they were 3-1-1 on Oct. 21, 1978. . . . Mark 
