<HEADLINE>
<P>
PIECE ON ENVIRONMENTAL INDUSTRY MISLED READERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It was with a great sense of disappointment and frustration that I and many 
other members of the California environmental industry read the article "Green 
Tape: Environmental Technology's Reality Falls Short of Hype" (Sept. 20). The 
article left readers with the misimpression that the California environmental 
technology industry is not a healthy component of our state's economy and that 
the state government is not doing anything to assist the industry.Nothing could 
be further from the truth. 
</P>
<P>
 California's environmental industry is made up of over 10,000 companies that 
employ approximately 180,000 Californians and generate close to $20 billion in 
annual revenues. The industry is the acknowledged worldwide leader in providing 
state-of-the-art environmental solutions in domestic and foreign markets. 
</P>
<P>
 Despite a severe recession that has affected all sectors of California's 
economy, the environmental industry continues to be a vibrant and positive 
contributor to job creation and export development for the state. 
</P>
<P>
 It is an industry with a varied range of experiences, but one that continues 
to grow and mature, and that represents a critical component of California's 
new economy. 
</P>
<P>
 BRIAN A. RUNKEL 
</P>
<P>
 Executive Director 
</P>
<P>
 California Environmental 
</P>
<P>
 Business Council 
</P>
</TEXT>
