<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: AWARDS: JOHN WAYNE AUXILIARY TO HONOR FOUNDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sandy Cohen will receive a Woman of Achievement Angel Award Wednesday in 
recognition of her work for the John Wayne Cancer Institute Auxiliary. 
</P>
<P>
 The auxiliary, co-founded by Cohen in 1983, is a fund-raising and volunteer 
arm of the institute. Since it was established, the auxiliary has raised more 
than $4 million for the institute's research. 
</P>
<P>
 Cohen is also a regular volunteer at the Institute's Breast Center, where she 
was treated for breast cancer several years ago. 
</P>
<P>
 The luncheon will be held at the Regent Beverly Wilshire and is open to the 
public. A $75-per-person donation is required. 
</P>
</TEXT>
