<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; INDONESIA; REMAINS OF U.S. WWII PILOT FOUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The remains of an American pilot killed during World War II have been found in 
Indonesia's Irian Jaya province, the official Antara news agency said.Villagers 
found the skeletal remains inside the wreckage of a fighter plane in a heavily 
forested area, the agency quoted a local military official as saying. The 
pilot's remains were flown to the United States. His identity was not known. 
</P>
