<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA CORNER: FESTIVALS, FEASTS & FAIRS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 LAKE ARROWHEAD -- German-style festivities fill the Village Festival Area for 
the 10th annual Fall Fling/Oktoberfest Celebration, Saturdays-Sundays through 
Oct. 30. 11 a.m.-5 p.m. Free admission. (909) 336-3274. 
</P>
<P>
 HALF MOON BAY -- More fall fun awaits at the Art and Pumpkin Festival, 10 
a.m.-5 p.m. Oct. 15-16.Compete in pumpkin-carving and pumpkin pie-eating 
contests and taste an assortment of pumpkin foods. Also guaranteed to make you 
see orange: the Great Pumpkin Parade, arts and crafts and entertainment. Free. 
On Main Street, downtown. Choose a pumpkin from any of the patches in the 
surrounding area. (415) 726-9652. 
</P>
<P>
 PERRIS -- The 48th annual Farmers Fair and Expo is themed "We'll Stirrup Some 
Fun," Oct. 15-23. Featured: Horse shows, carnivals, racing pigs, concerts and 
more. Monday-Wednesday and Friday, 5-11 p.m.; Thursday, noon-10 p.m.; 
Saturdays, 11 a.m.-11 p.m.; Sundays, 11 a.m.-10 p.m. At the Lake Perris 
Fairgrounds. (909) 657-4221. 
</P>
<P>
 BAKERSFIELD -- The Village Artisan's Medieval Faire is Oct. 15-16 in Central 
Park, 19th and R streets. Costumed participants offer arts and crafts and 
ethnic foods, and entertainment is staged by a Shakespearean troupe, dancing 
groups and others. Free. (805) 328-1943. 
</P>
<P>
 ESCONDIDO -- A huge assortment of arts and crafts vendors sell their wares at 
the sixth annual Escondido Fall Street Faire, 9 a.m.-5 p.m. Oct. 16. Free. On 
Grand Avenue, between Center City Parkway and Juniper Street. (619) 483-5373. 
</P>
<P>
 Call listed phone numbers for directions. MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
</TEXT>
