April, 1992, when he closed Congress and the courts with military backing and 
began ruling by fiat. Four Cabinet ministers resigned, amid speculation that 
they will run for Parliament. Those resigning were Absalon Vasquez 
(Agriculture), Jaime Freundt (Health), Jorge Trelles (Education) and Dante 
Cordova (Transport, Communications, Housing and Construction). 
