<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: NEWBURY PARK; HAZARDOUS-WASTE PICKUPS SCHEDULED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County's first hazardous-waste collection program designed solely for 
small businesses will begin in Newbury Park this fall. 
</P>
<P>
 Business owners have until Oct. 17 to sign up for the program, which will 
allow safe disposal of paint, pool chemicals, batteries, pesticides and other 
toxic material generated in the workplace. Appointments are available only to 
businesses in Thousand Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the city's environmental program analyst, Carolyn 
Greene, at 449-2472. STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
</TEXT>
