<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 DIE IN SEPARATE TRAFFIC ACCIDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VIVIEN LOU CHEN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two people were killed Saturday in separate traffic accidents in Valencia and 
Saugus, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Shortly after 3 p.m. in Valencia, a 40-year-old woman died when the car in 
which she was a passenger was rear-ended by another vehicle and burst into 
flames on the northbound Golden State Freeway near Valencia Boulevard, the 
California Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman was identified as Barbara Moore of Pacoima. The driver, Edward 
Clayton, 44, apparently noticed he had a flat tire and was trying to pull onto 
the right shoulder at 2 m.p.h. when the vehicle was hit, a CHP spokeswoman 
said. Clayton and the driver of the second car were taken to Henry Mayo Newhall 
Memorial Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 About an hour later in Saugus, motorist Michael Murphy, 18, of Saugus was 
killed after speeding his car through a red light at Seco Canyon Road and 
Decoro Drive, witnesses said. 
</P>
<P>
 Murphy's vehicle collided head-on with a second car, struck a telephone pole 
and flipped over, sheriff's deputies said. The driver of the second car, Kari 
Liekkio, 56, of Aqua Dulce suffered bruises and passenger Marcia Liekko, 54, 
suffered a possible injured neck, authorities said. Both were also taken to 
Henry Mayo Newhall Memorial Hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
