<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN KILLED WHEN VAN HITS VEHICLE ON FAIRVIEW STREET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 One man was killed late Friday when a van collided with another vehicle as the 
van's driver tried to change lanes on South Fairview Street, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The van's driver, 28-year-old Antonio Camacho of Santa Ana, was arrested on 
suspicion of felony drunk driving and suspicion of manslaughter, Sgt. Eric 
Vedborg said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, who had not been identified Saturday, was riding in a 1974 Ford 
van that was traveling north when Camacho tried to change lanes in the 1300 
block of South Fairview shortly before midnight, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The van struck the other vehicle, which was traveling in the same direction, 
and then crashed into a light pole, Vedborg said. No one in the other vehicle 
was injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
