 -- West Texas A&M's Grady Benton passed for 451 yards and seven touchdowns in 
a 70-44 victory over Western New Mexico. But the Arizona State transfer was 
outdone by Alfred Montez, who passed for 614 yards and four touchdowns for 
Western New Mexico. Benton completed 33 of 48 passes and Montez 39 of 63 as the 
teams combined for 1,494 yards. 
</P>
