<P>
 -- Valdosta State quarterback Chris Hatcher became the career touchdown pass 
leader in Division II as he threw five in a 38-7 victory over New Haven. 
Hatcher's 94 scoring passes broke the mark of 93 set by Doug Williams, who 
played at Grambling from 1974-77. AND THEY DIDN'T ENJOY IT 
</P>
