<HEADLINE>
<P>
VILLAGE CHRISTIAN'S FIVE FIELD GOALS TOO MUCH FOR SCC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Village Christian's Ignacio Brache, who kicked field goals of 35, 42, 48, 55 
and 56 yards in the Crusaders' 29-14 victory over Southern California Christian 
on Friday, is still striving for his ultimate goal -- a Southern Section record 
for the longest field goal. Oak Park's Eric Affholter set the record with a 
64-yarder in 1982. 
</P>
<P>
 "Once we crossed the (50-yard line), I didn't want to go any further because 
he was so hot," Village Christian Coach Mike Plaisance said. "I thought about 
taking two delay-of-game penalties -- all of those things go through your mind 
-- but, I didn't want (SCC Coach Bert Esposito) to think we were running up the 
score. We definitely wanted to give him a chance to break the record." Village 
Christian is 2-3. 
</P>
<P>
 Brache broke his Division X record with the 56-yard kick, which is two yards 
longer than last year's record. His five field goals also tie a Southern 
Section record held by four kickers for most field goals in a single game and 
break a school record held by Jason Jones, who kicked four in 1987. 
</P>
<P>
 Ken Buhler rushed for 156 yards in 18 carries, including a 78-yard touchdown 
run, for Southern California Christian (1-4). 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story; Prep Sports 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA100994-0340 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 087186 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
October 9, 1994, Sunday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 15; Column 3 
</P>
</SECTION>
