<HEADLINE>
<P>
BALANCED OREGON STATE DEFEATS NORTHRIDGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Oregon State women's volleyball team used a balanced attack to defeat Cal 
State Northridge, 15-12, 15-9, 11-15, 15-10, Saturday night in a nonconference 
match at Corvallis, Oregon. 
</P>
<P>
 The Matadors (10-7) were led by Missy Clements, who had a match-high 20 kills, 
but were undone by 31 team hitting errors to finish with a hitting percentage 
of only .103. 
</P>
<P>
 Matador Aimee Stone notched 12 kills but had 14 errors. Teammate Heather 
Anderson added 11 kills, and setter Kathleen Shannon had 39 set assists. 
</P>
<P>
 Oregon State is 11-6. 
</P>
</TEXT>
