<HEADLINE>
<P>
USTA WOMEN'S SENIOR HARDCOURT; LAGUNA BEACH'S CLARK CAPTURES SINGLES TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Laguna Beach's Doris Clark swept Piedmont's June Gay, 6-2, 6-2, to capture the 
championship of the U.S. Tennis Assn.National Women's Hardcourt senior tennis 
tournament Saturday at the Newport Beach Tennis Club. 
</P>
<P>
 Clark, the top-seeded in the 65-year-old division, advanced to the final by 
beating Elaine Mason of Fresno, 7-5, 6-1, on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills' Charlotte Decker and Los Angeles' Alice Beckenbach fell to Dodo 
Cheney of Santa Monica and Pat Stuhler of Brielle, N.J., 6-1, 6-1, in the 75s 
doubles final. 
</P>
<P>
 Cheney, the top-seeded in the 75s singles, swept Stuhler, 6-1, 6-3, in the 
final. 
</P>
