<TEXT>
<P>
 Long Beach Wilson's Adam Wright scored the game-winning goal with 2 minutes 5 
seconds remaining to lead the Bruins to a 10-9 nonleague water polo victory 
over host Corona del Mar on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Trailing, 9-8, Wilson (8-1), ranked No. 3 in Southern Section's Division I, 
tied the score when Rick Westberg beat Corona del Mar goalie Doug Jetton with 
2:40 left to play. 
</P>
<P>
