<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; THOUSAND OAKS RUNS RAMPANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK CARULLI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Thousand Oaks High boys' and girls' cross-country teams dominated the 
South Valley Invitational at Huntington Beach Central Park on Saturday, 
illustrating why they are the state's top-ranked teams. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks scored 26 points to win the boys' race. Chula Vista was second 
with 75, followed by San Diego Hoover (98), San Diego (157) and Point Loma 
(158). 
</P>
<P>
 Keith O'Dougherty of Thousand Oaks won in 15 minutes 21 seconds. Teammate Jeff 
Fischer was third in 15:50 and Todd Disney was fourth in 15:55. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancer girls scored 29 points to easily defeat second-place Green Valley, 
Nevada (119). La Jolla (129) was third, followed by Cheyenne, Nevada (132), and 
Huntington Beach 159. 
</P>
<P>
 Kim Mortensen won the girls' race, in 18:33, 40 seconds ahead of the 
second-place finisher. Teammate Bridget Roy finished third in 19:21 and Katie 
Scherrei was sixth in 19:44. WOMEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran 5, Claremont-Mudd 0 -- Jill Gallegos scored three goals to lead 
the Regals (10-3, 7-0) in a Southern California Athletic Conference match at 
Cal Lutheran. Carla Crawford and Emily Kanney also scored. 
</P>
<P>
 Goalies Kim Carver and Laura Corsi combined for the shutout. HIGH SCHOOL 
FOOTBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Kilpatrick 13, Whittier Christian 12 -- Mario Qualls scored on a two-yard run 
as time expired, giving Kilpatrick a dramatic nonleague victory at Whittier 
College. 
</P>
<P>
 Qualls' run capped a 14-play, 63-yard drive in which the Mustangs converted 
two fourth downs. Cesar Cuevas passed to Henry Flowers for 27 yards on fourth 
and 24 during the drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Kilpatrick (4-1) trailed, 12-0, entering the fourth quarter, but Qualls scored 
on an 11-yard run with 11:21. Qualls finished with 124 yards in 19 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Cathedral 21, St. Genevieve 19 -- Travis Jackson scored on a one-yard run with 
one minute to play to prevent St. Genevieve (0-5, 0-2) from winning in a Santa 
Fe League game at Birmingham High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Valiants overcame an eight-point deficit to take a 19-15 lead early in the 
fourth quarter on touchdown runs of 35 yards on a reverse by Eric Tapia and one 
yard by Rickey Estrada. Estrada also scored on an 11-yard run. 8-MAN FOOTBALL 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. Lutheran 26, Ribet Academy 16 -- L.A. Lutheran running back Rick Lehr 
scored three touchdowns in a Heritage League game at L.A. Lutheran. 
</P>
<P>
 Lehr returned a third-quarter kickoff 73 yards for a score to give the Lions 
(3-2, 1-0) a 14-8 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Faith Baptist 51, Santa Maria Valley Christian 6 -- Colby Carpenter and Tywane 
Patterson each scored three touchdowns for host Faith Baptist in a nonleague 
game. 
</P>
<P>
 Carpenter gained 115 yards in 11 carries and scored on runs of 40, eight and 
three yards. Patterson added a 12-yard touchdown run and caught two scoring 
passes. FRANK CARULLI 
</P>
