ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: NEW VICE PRESIDENT AT CALIFORNIA STATE BANK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thomas M. Shepherd has been appointed senior vice president and branch manager 
of California State Bank's Newport Beach office. He was formerly senior vice 
president and loan administrator for Commerce Bank. 
</P>
<P>
 * Phillip L. Luecht Jr. has been appointed vice president in charge of sales 
and the Insurance Services division for the Costa Mesa office of Johnson & 
Higgins. Luecht has been with the insurance broker since 1985, holding a number 
of positions including property/casualty broker, deputy casualty manager, sales 
manager and liaison officer for the London office. 
</P>
<P>
 * Judi A. Lapin has been appointed vice president of corporate marketing for 
Donahue Schriber, a Newport Beach shopping center development and management 
firm. She was formerly president of Judi Lapin & Associates, which specialized 
in the shopping center and tourism industries. 
</P>
<P>
 * Thomas Silber has been appointed president of Bivar Inc., an Irvine 
manufacturer of electronic assembly hardware. Silber joined the company in 1989 
as national sales manager and was appointed vice president of sales and 
marketing in 1991. 
</P>
<P>
 * Kevin J. Burkhalter has been promoted to senior vice president in the 
Century City office of Johnson Capital Group in Irvine. Before joining the 
company in 1989, he was with Weyerhaeuser Mortgage Co. for four years. 
</P>
