<HEADLINE>
<P>
CASTELLANOS' INTERCEPTION LIFTS FREMONT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SMITH, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fremont Coach Taja Rodisha has been preaching senior leadership to his players 
all season, and that's exactly what Gus Castellanos gave him in a Friday 
afternoon game against Jefferson. 
</P>
<P>
 The senior defensive back's interception with 1:51 in the fourth quarter 
sealed the Pathfinders' 12-7 Southeastern Conference win. 
</P>
<P>
 "I've been telling the seniors that we need someone to step up and provide 
leadership," Rodisha said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Fortunately, that's what we got." 
</P>
<P>
 Castellanos also scored Fremont's first touchdown on an 11-yard reception from 
quarterback Robert Loera in the third quarter. Delante Walker's 25-yard 
touchdown run put Fremont ahead 12-0 at the start of the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 After quarterback Larry Roberson's four-yard touchdown run brought Jefferson 
within 12-7 at the 5:53 mark, Fremont turned the ball over on downs and the 
Democrats marched down the field. 
</P>
<P>
 But Roberson's pass to Isaac Hatley was batted in the air and caught by 
Castellanos, who returned it to the Fremont 25-yard line. 
</P>
<P>
 Jefferson's offense couldn't produce consistent drives against Fremont's 
defense, amassing only 74 yards in total offense to Fremont's 282. Hatley was 
held to 27 yards in 11 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Records: Fremont 4-1; Jefferson 1-4 
</P>
<P>
 Next week: Fremont BYE; Jefferson at Locke. 
</P>
</TEXT>
